"title": "5509: rulers",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5509",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Officials who, acting as God's servants, govern others and exercise authority over them. Also the originators of the laws of their realms. In the NT, rulers are also spiritual powers.</p>\n<h2>Officials exercising authority over people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:25\">MAT 20:25</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:42\">MRK 10:42</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:20\">2CH 23:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:2\">PSA 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:2\">PRO 28:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:1\">ISA 16:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:7\">DAN 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:10\">HOS 13:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:52\">LUK 1:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:11\">LUK 12:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:27\">ACT 7:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:14\">EXO 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:6-1Cor2:8\">1CO 2:6–2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Godly rulers in foreign lands</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:16-Ps105:22\">PSA 105:16–105:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:48\">DAN 2:48</a></p>\n<h3>Importance of submitting to civil authorities</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:3\">ROM 13:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:1\">TIT 3:1</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of rulers</h2>\n<h3>Rulers of areas apart from Israel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:16\">GEN 25:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:2\">GEN 34:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:41\">GEN 41:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:8\">GEN 45:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:31\">2CH 32:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:2\">EZK 28:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek31:11\">EZK 31:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:1\">DAN 9:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:10\">ACT 7:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:18\">ACT 7:18</a></p>\n<h3>The five Philistine rulers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:3\">JOS 13:3</a></strong> <em>The Hebrew word translated “rulers” is related to the word “tyrant” and is only used of Philistines rulers.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:3\">JDG 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:11\">JDG 15:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:18\">JDG 16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam5:8\">1SA 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:16\">1SA 6:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam29:2\">1SA 29:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:19\">1CH 12:19</a></p>\n<h3>The king of Israel is referred to as a ruler</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:1-2Sam5:2\">2SA 5:1–5:2</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:1-1Chr11:2\">1CH 11:1–11:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:34-1Kgs1:35\">1KI 1:34–1:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:34\">1KI 11:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:2\">1CH 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:1\">MIC 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>Other rulers of Israel (or parts of it)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:26\">1KI 22:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:25\">2CH 18:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:9\">NEH 3:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:23\">ISA 1:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:21\">JER 30:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:1\">MIC 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:6\">MAT 2:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:18\">LUK 18:18</a></p>\n<h3>One of three groups that made up the Sanhedrin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:5\">ACT 4:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:13\">LUK 23:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:20\">LUK 24:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:48\">JHN 7:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:8\">ACT 4:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:27\">ACT 13:27</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is described as a ruler</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5\">REV 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:6\">MAT 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:2\">MIC 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:14\">REV 3:14</a></p>\n<h3>God the Father is also called a ruler</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:15\">1TI 6:15</a></p>\n<h2>A ruler as the originator of the laws of his realm</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:15\">PRO 8:15</a></p>\n<h2>Rulers are appointed by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1-Rom13:2\">ROM 13:1–13:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:21\">2SA 6:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:7-2Sam7:8\">2SA 7:7–7:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:6-1Chr17:7\">1CH 17:6–17:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:34\">1KI 11:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:7\">PSA 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:28\">ISA 44:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:6\">JER 27:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:38\">DAN 2:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:17\">DAN 4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:11\">JHN 19:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:17\">ROM 9:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:16\">EXO 9:16</a></p>\n<h2>Rulers are God's servants</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:4\">ROM 13:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:1\">ISA 45:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:9\">JER 25:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer43:10\">JER 43:10</a></p>\n<h2>Rulers are God's representatives</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps58:1\">PSA 58:1</a></strong> <em>The Hebrew word translated “rulers” literally means “gods” a title given to those whose position called for them to act as earthly representatives of God's heavenly court.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps82:1\">PSA 82:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:34-John10:35\">JHN 10:34–10:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps82:6\">PSA 82:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:5\">ACT 23:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:28\">EXO 22:28</a></p>\n<h2>Rulers as spiritual powers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:10\">EPH 3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:21\">EPH 1:21</a> <em>In the NT, rulers are spiritual powers, some of whom exercise a Satanic authority</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:12\">EPH 6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16\">COL 1:16</a></p>\n<h2>Synagogue rulers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:22\">MRK 5:22</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:18\">MAT 9:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:41\">LUK 8:41</a> <em>The ruler of a synagogue looked after the building and supervised the worship in it.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:35-Mark5:36\">MRK 5:35–5:36</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:49-Luke8:50\">LUK 8:49–8:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:38\">MRK 5:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:14\">LUK 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:15\">ACT 13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:8\">ACT 18:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:17\">ACT 18:17</a></p>",
